Question, is staking safe? What if the validator gets hacked or goes offline ?

When you delegate to a validator, the validator is using your Tao to earn additional rewards and increase its position on the network.  The validator does not have access to your staked Tao and cannot take them, even if operating maliciously: your Tao is never forfeited nor are the additional gains you receive in the form of Tao at a rate of 82% of that validator’s rate. 

If the validator goes down, both you and the validator stop earning Tao. At that point, you can unstake your Tao (including any gains you earned while validator was running) and the validator keeps their portion of the additional gains from your your Tao (18%).  Your original stake and rewards earned are never in jeopardy and can be unstaked at any time.
